{"meta": {"centerNodeId": "taxonomy-species-myzomela-prawiradilagae", "centerNodeType": "taxonomy", "generatedAt": "2026-05-28T16:28:22", "includedNodeCount": 3, "includedLinkCount": 2, "layoutMode": "precomputed-static"}, "center": {"id": "taxonomy-species-myzomela-prawiradilagae", "name": "Alor myzomela", "type": "taxonomy"}, "nodes": [{"id": "bird-alor-myzomela-7d9cd1ea", "name": "Alor myzomela", "englishName": "Alor myzomela", "latinName": "Myzomela prawiradilagae", "type": "bird", "status": "EN", "summary": "The Alor myzomela (Myzomela prawiradilagae) is a species of bird in the family Meliphagidae, the honeyeaters. It is endemic to the Indonesian island of Alor, where it is the only representative member of the genus Myzomela. It is named after Dewi Malia Prawiradilaga, an ornithologist at the Indonesian Institute of Science and one of the first leading female Indonesian ornithologists. Taxonomy It closely resembles and is most closely related to the Wetar myzomela (M. kuehni) of the adjacent island of Wetar. However, it noticeably differs in its calls and morphology. Distribution The Alor myzomela is restricted to a few montane areas of Alor Island, where it lives in Eucalyptus woodlands primarily composed of white gum (Eucalyptus alba) and Timor mountain gum (Eucalyptus urophylla), as well as wattles (Acacia sp.) and sheoak (Casuarina junghuhniana). This restricted distribution is in contrast to its close relative M. kuehni, which is among the most common birds on its islands; this difference may be due to the different habitat requirements of the two species. Diet They have been observed feeding on the fruit of Himalayan chokeberry (Photinia integrifolia) in small groups along with ashy-bellied white-eyes (Zosterops citrinellus). They also feed on the flowers of Eucalyptus alba, as well as occasionally insects. Threats This species is at high risk due to its severely restricted and fragmented distribution, which is compounded by the growing human population on the island. Thus, it has been proposed that the species be classified as Endangered on the IUCN Red List. References", "shortSummary": "The Alor myzomela (Myzomela prawiradilagae) is a species of bird in the family Meliphagidae, the honeyeaters. It is endemic to the Indonesi…", "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/a/ab/Alor_Myzomela_imported_from_iNaturalist_photo_331308197_on_25_July_2024.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-myzomela", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-myzomela-prawiradilagae", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-myzomela", "species": "taxonomy-species-myzomela-prawiradilagae"}, "expandable": true, "x": 465.4, "y": -601.12, "z": -151.59}, {"id": "taxonomy-genus-myzomela", "name": "Myzomela", "latinName": "Myzomela", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "Myzomela（Myzomela）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联41种鸟类，如Drab myzomela、White-chinned myzomela、Ruby-throated myzomela等41种鸟类。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 41, "x": 516.53, "y": 341.18, "z": 4.53}, {"id": "taxonomy-species-myzomela-prawiradilagae", "name": "Alor myzomela", "latinName": "Myzomela prawiradilagae", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "species", "summary": "Alor myzomela（Myzomela prawiradilagae）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联1种鸟类，如Alor myzomela。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 1, "x": 465.4, "y": -601.12, "z": -150.89}], "links": [{"key": "bird-alor-myzomela-7d9cd1ea__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-myzomela-prawiradilagae", "source": "bird-alor-myzomela-7d9cd1ea", "target": "taxonomy-species-myzomela-prawiradilagae", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 中的种字段补充。"}, {"key": "taxonomy-species-myzomela-prawiradilagae__belongs_to_genus__taxonomy-genus-myzomela", "source": "taxonomy-species-myzomela